Starship Name Ideas:

Starship Experience- The first starship to travel into space and orbit the moon. This will be the one to fly billionaire Yusaku Maezawa.

Starship Enterprise- The first starship to bring humans to Mars. “Boldly going where no man has gone before.”

Starship Explorer- A tribute to the final concept art for the Space Shuttle, which was named Explorer.

Starship Voyager- Named after the Voyager 1 probe that was sent on a mission into space, never to return.

Starship Angelus- Latin for angel. This
commemorates the men and women who lost their lives in the name of space exploration. Apollo 1, Challenger, and Columbia.

Starship Constitution- Named after the U.S.S. Constitution, a war ship known for its sturdy construction. Fought in the First Barbary War and the War of 1812. This ship is still afloat today after 213 years.

Tim. . . how far we’ve come. I remember 1966 or so. . . watching on TV, live coverage of the recovery of a Gemini capsule from somewhere in the Pacific Ocean. . . thinking, wow, live TV from thousands of miles away.

In 1953, we had been shown the Queen Elizabeth II coronation “almost live”. . . on TV, from a movie film that had been flown across the Atlantic Ocean by an aircraft. . . possibly a Jet. . . but our family had emigrated from The Netherlands to Canada in 1951 by a four-engined Lockheed Constellation, at that a time a beautiful triple tailed piston aircraft. . . (An amazing journey for a six-year-old curious boy).
